Sentencas: A-site deficient perovskite La0.57Sr0.15TiO3 (LSTO) materials are synthesized by a modified polyacrylamide gel route.
Titulo: Optimization of the electrochemical performance of a Ni/Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ-impregnated La0.57Sr0.15TiO3 anode in hydrogen

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction pattern of LSTO indicates an orthorhombic structure.
Titulo: Optimization of the electrochemical performance of a Ni/Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ-impregnated La0.57Sr0.15TiO3 anode in hydrogen

Sentencas: The thermal expansion coefficient of LSTO is 10.0 x 10(-6) K-1 at 600 degrees C in 5%H-2/Ar.
Titulo: Optimization of the electrochemical performance of a Ni/Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ-impregnated La0.57Sr0.15TiO3 anode in hydrogen

Sentencas: LSTO shows an electrical conductivity of 2 S cm(-1) at 600 degrees C in 3%H2O/H-2.
Titulo: Optimization of the electrochemical performance of a Ni/Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ-impregnated La0.57Sr0.15TiO3 anode in hydrogen

Sentencas: A new composite material, containing the porous LSTO backbone impregnated with small amounts of Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-delta (CGO) (3.4-8.3 wt.%) and Ni/Cu (2.0-63 wt.%), is investigated as an alternative anode for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Optimization of the electrochemical performance of a Ni/Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ-impregnated La0.57Sr0.15TiO3 anode in hydrogen

Sentencas: Because of the substantial electrocatalytic activity of the fine and well-dispersed Ni particles on the surface of the ceramic framework, the polarization resistance of 6.3%Ni-8.3%CGO-LSTO anode reaches 0.73 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C in 3%H2O/H-2.
Titulo: Optimization of the electrochemical performance of a Ni/Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ-impregnated La0.57Sr0.15TiO3 anode in hydrogen

Sentencas: In order to further improve the anodic performance, corn starch and carbon black are used as pore-formers to optimize the microstructure of anodes.
Titulo: Optimization of the electrochemical performance of a Ni/Ce0.9Gd0.1O2-δ-impregnated La0.57Sr0.15TiO3 anode in hydrogen
